The paper discusses a method for improving open-domain question answering by creating an indexable representation of document phrases. This involves capturing syntactic, semantic, and lexical information of phrases and eliminating the need for pipeline filtering of context documents. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Databases (cs.DB).
